byline.original: By MOHAMMED IBRAHIM and JEFFREY GETTLEMAN
byline.contributor: Mohamed Ibrahim reported from Mogadishu, and Jeffrey Gettleman from Nairobi, Kenya.

snippet: A blast in Mogadishu, Somalia’s capital, killed more than 50 people and possibly signaled a comeback for the Islamic militant group known as the Shabab.
lead_paragraph: A blast in Mogadishu, Somalia’s capital, killed more than 50 people and possibly signaled a comeback for the Islamic militant group known as the Shabab.

headline.main: Truck Bomb Kills Dozens in Somalia’s Capital
headline.print_headline: Bomb Kills Dozens in Somalia’s Capital and Signals Return of Militant Group
